p.50 "Wrenched accent" has been also applied by prosodists to what I call "tilting" (see further).

p.51 Spondaic

No spondaic words can be said to exist in Englishâ€”unless a very special pause is made between the syllables, or the compound mouthed with a good deal of didactic rumination and slow jaw work. The word "heartbreak" is a trochee at heart. True spondees do not occur in English metrical verse but can be imitated in cadential or pausative verse:





